  "prompt": "How do you stop a sunburn from peeling?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to help prevent or minimize sunburn peeling:\n\n1. Hydrate your skin\n- Drink plenty of water\n- Apply moisturizer frequently\n- Use aloe vera gel to soothe and hydrate skin\n\n2. Keep the skin moisturized\n- Use fragrance-free, gentle moisturizers\n- Apply moisturizer while skin is still damp\n- Look for lotions with ingredients like hyaluronic acid or glycerin\n\n3. Do not pick or peel skin\n- Let skin naturally shed\n- Avoid pulling or scratching peeling skin\n- Use soft, cool compresses to help skin heal\n\n4. Protect healing skin\n- Stay out of direct sunlight\n- Wear loose, breathable clothing\n- Use sunscreen with high SPF when outdoors\n\n5. Additional treatments\n- Take cool showers\n- Use healing ointments like petroleum jelly\n- Consider over-the-counter hydrocortisone cream for inflammation\n\n6. Support healing from inside\n- Eat foods rich in antioxidants\n- Take vitamin E supplements\n- Consume foods with omega-3 fatty acids\n\nPrevention is always best: Always use sunscreen and limit sun exposure to avoid sunburns in the first place.",
